  title: `Utilitarianism and the Ethics of Warfare Technology`,
  subtitle: `Counting lives, measuring outcomes, deploying drones.`,
  summary: `Classical utilitarianism meets autonomous weapons. The calculus, its temptations, and the places where "the greatest good for the greatest number" breaks.`,
  learningGoals: [`Apply act and rule utilitarianism to concrete deployment decisions.`, `Identify who the "greatest number" includes — and whom the math quietly excludes.`, `Evaluate the moral implications of automating lethality at scale.`],
  shortStoryTitle: `The Greater Good Bureau`,
  heroImage: '/textbook/chapter-05.svg',
